genresAdvancedInfo.name: panpipe
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Panpipe, also known as pan flute, is a wind instrument made up of multiple pipes of varying lengths. It is commonly associated with traditional Andean music, but is also used in other genres such as New Age and world music. The sound of the panpipe is haunting and ethereal, and is often used to evoke a sense of nature and spirituality.
